click to enlargeTargeted at executives in the public and private sectors, civil society, academia and emerging entrepreneurs, the title has a strong focus on communicating and sharing inspiring, elevating, encouraging, empowering, positive, solution-driven business angled storytelling.It also shies away from negative reporting, noting the dynamics and challenges that society has experienced throughout the ecosystem. The digital business magazine is owned by the holding company, Atlantic Lionsa. And it’s been enhanced to denote the reimagined and reconfigured ecosystem as repositioned between nations with a strong focus on how South Africa, the African continent and the global community would achieve more through collaboration, interdependence, mutual respect, sharing and by being changemakers. A publications company, Atlantic Lionsa has been repositioned to be the centre of excellence and reference for regenerative, inspiring, enlightening and digitally-biased storytelling. “We are borne out of a need to retain integrity, excellence, creativity, collaborative partnerships, humility, sustainability, respect, interdependence, shared leadership and quality over quantity.This as we spread our wings to influence and redefine the digital publication space…” says Davlynne Lidbetter, founder and managing director at The Elevation Business Magazine Africa.